<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25989</anchor> <rss>anon.248.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.248</addr>  <route>anon.248.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>We must check that <tex>a \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup _{p: \lnot { \mathopen {} \left ( a =  \bot \right ) \mathclose {}} }a</tex>. By assumption, it suffices to check that <tex>\bigsqcup _{p: \mathsf { pos } \, a}a \sqsubseteq \bigsqcup _{p: \lnot { \mathopen {} \left ( a= \bot \right ) \mathclose {}} }a</tex>, which follows because <link href="jms-002H.xml" type="local" addr="jms-002H" title="The bottom element is not positive">the bottom element is not positive</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25990</anchor> <rss>jms-002N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-002N</addr>  <route>jms-002N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Positively generated elements are non-negatively generated</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>a</tex> be a <link href="jms-002F.xml" type="local" addr="jms-002F" title="Positively generated elements">positively generated element</link> of a <link href="jms-001S.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001S" title="Pointed dcpo">pointed</link> dcpo <tex>A</tex>. Then <tex>a</tex> is also <link href="jms-002J.xml" type="local" addr="jms-002J" title="Non-negatively generated elements">non-negatively generated</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25991</anchor> <rss>jms-002H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-002H</addr>  <route>jms-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>2</month> <day>16</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The bottom element is not positive</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The bottom element <tex>\bot</tex> of a pointed dcpo <tex>A</tex> is not <link href="jms-001M.xml" type="local" addr="jms-001M" title="The positive elements of a pointed dcpo">positive</link>.</p>
 
   
   <tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="false" numbered="true" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25992</anchor> <rss>anon.250.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.250</addr>  <route>anon.250.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
  <p>Suppose that <tex>\bot</tex> was positive. The empty set <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ \right \} \mathclose {}} \subseteq  A</tex> is semidirected and <tex>\bot \sqsubseteq   \bigsqcup { \mathopen {} \left \{ \right \} \mathclose {}} = \bot</tex>, but nonetheless <tex>{ \mathopen {} \left \{ \right \} \mathclose {}}</tex> is not inhabited.</p>
</mainmatter> </tree>
 
